trend_summary: From earliest to latest scenes the peninsula stays predominantly wooded, but incremental change occurs: a sand-quarry near the south triples in area, new cul-de-sac suburbs extend from existing neighbourhoods and the highway, while several farm plots vanish under trees. Overall footprint grows slowly, giving a sparse, largely suburban landscape.
notable_changes: Southern quarry/mining pit expands markedly, clearing additional forest and farmland.

Central farmland parcels gradually revert to woodland or low vegetation.
